      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NANGAR WALLY (7) was in the placings last time but shapes well for this on his brilliant win three back, getting around this track over 450m in 25.13. Has the ability and looks hard to top. SO REFINED (1) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in three starts, including two wins. Placed last time (25.42) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 2.25 lengths. Looks well placed here and among the chances. VIN ROSE (2) missed the frame latest when sixth at Wentworth Park (30.42) but scored three back at Q Parklands (29.78). Scored previously at this trip. Leading chance. ISLE OF LACHLAN (3) was out of the money at this circuit last start but can make amends.",
